You can use this open metal shelf to put your favorite books, CDs, crafts, photo albums, potted plants, basket, toys, collectibles, also keep your home, apartment tidy and organized. [Stable & Sturdy]: The slim book shelves is made of high-quality P2 MDF board and solid black metal frame. 2 X-bars and anti-tip kits design on the side further enhances the stability. Equipped with 4 adjustable feet which can stay stable even on uneven floor and prevent you scratch the floor by moving. Each board has a load-bearing capacity of 30lbs. Your ideal furniture choice!

[Easy to Assemble]: 5 tier shelving unit overall dimension is 10.6"D x 14.9"W x 55.1"H. Easy to follow instructions including, the hardware and tools included and each accessory is labeled for easy installation. We provides customer service before and after purchase. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great storage for tight spaces
reviews.reviewText: If you have a smaller area but still need a bookshelf, this is the shelf for you. It has 5 tiers so it will hold lots of books, photos and misc. Items. 2 of the shelves have a back piece, with the others open on all sides. It is designed with a black metal frame that is cross braced for stability, and rustic brown wooden shelves that are very easy to clean. The unit is only 10.6” deep so it won’t stick out very far into the room. The shelves are 14” long so it can squeeze into a small space. It is 55” tall so it can accommodate taller items on the shelves. This bookshelf unit has a very simplistic design that would blend well with most any decor so you can use it almost anywhere. It would also make a great storage piece in a bathroom, too. I really like this versatile shelf. Lots of storage in a small space, and you also get an anti-tip stabilizer strap for safety.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pay attention to the instructions or you'll be taking it apart to swap the legs around
reviews.reviewText: The shelf is nice and sturdy and holds a decent amount of weight as well. I like the rustic brown color and the paint is nice and even on the metal pieces which makes for an attractive piece of furniture. The adjustable feet are a huge plus as my floor is slightly uneven so I was able to adjust the shelf to have it stand level. There is also an anti tip kit included but I don't see a need for it as the shelf is very sturdy on it's own, especially if you put heavier items on the bottom shelves. One thing I will note is there are covers for the screws but if you install the screws properly they will countersink to far to allow the covers to attach. Not a big deal to me personally as I have items on the shelf that covers the screws anyways, the caps would just make the shelf no longer flat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple design, looks good
reviews.reviewText: The parts of this shelf have a nice finish with a smooth texture on the sturdy metal structure and a textured wood veneer. My shelf arrived packaged well with no visible imperfections. The metal structure is rigid with additional cross bracing for added support. The shelves are thick with a heavy feel, which is good for the individual shelf strength and the overall balance of the unit. Even though it is sturdy, its height and narrowness make it a potential tipping hazard. I recommend using the wall anchor kit if children are around. The leveling feet are nice to remove any wobble. This is a nicely finished shelf with a modern look and quality materials.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Compact, nice looking
reviews.reviewText: This set of shelves wasn’t terrible to assemble, but man oh man do they have some adhesive on the little numbered stickers. I had to use a scraper to slowly and carefully scrape the stickers off each piece after it was assembled. I’m not sure why they had to use industrial glue type of stickers, but somehow there wasn’t damage to the surfaces (metal and wood both) after removal. Aside from that frustration, I really like this little shelf. It’s compact and fits into smaller spaces, and in my opinion, makes the space feel a bit larger. I have it in the corner of the hallway where anything bigger would be awkward to walk past. Two of the shelves are just over a foot tall, and two of them are just shy of a foot. The whole unit is around 4.5 feet. The circular shaped feet at the bottom of the unit rotate to easily adjust for uneven flooring.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice shelf
reviews.reviewText: My young son handed me items while I put this together. Took about an hour, maybe less. Instructions were fairly straightforward. It's a sturdy and nice shelf. The shelves are just tall enough for file folders and larger books and it's really helped to tidy up my office while also offering a polished look. Perfect size for a corner as well

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and unique! Super sturdy
reviews.reviewText: It's deceptively sturdy and was super easy to put together. Plenty of room for a surprising amount of books.I love the design, it's the most unique part of this piece that I think should be talked about more. It's a small thing, but I appreciate the fact that this bookshelf strayed away from the conventional ladder-like look of most bookshelves.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice shelf unit
reviews.reviewText: I have to say this is one of the assemble yourself pieces that I’ve put together that didn’t have a single issue. All the pieces were there, even included extra screws. All the parts were labeled. Instruction book was very clear on directions. Do pay attention to what side the labels are on. This makes a huge difference when putting it together. I assembled this by myself in about 30 minutes. It comes with a small screwdriver, but I would recommend using a full size one. I still have to peel the stickers off but I think this is a super cute piece!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love my new shelf. I feel like for the quality and sturdiness, this shelf is right on the money. Came packaged well and in perfect condition. No complaints. It was very simple to assemble and took me about an hour, with the "help" of a toddler. It even came with 4 little caps to put over the screws on the shelves that are above the back wall pieces. I call that attention to detail.The shelf might not be super ideal for many books, as there are no sides, just a pair of x bars overlapping the bottom 2 shelves that kind of hold books in when placed vertically. The shelves are not very long and may not effectively hold book ends without having them pushed over onto the ground.
